&s;eem to have the <HI>facies leucophlegmatica.</HI>
Perhaps, indeed, your di&s;order may be
<HI>$e$ematous,</HI> or gouty, or it may be the
<HI>lues venerea:</HI> If you have any rea&s;on
to flatter your&s;elf it is this la&s;t, &s;ir, I
will undertake to cure you with three
&s;mall pills, even if the di&s;ea&s;e &s;hould
have attained its utmo&s;t inveteracy.
Sir, it is an arcanum which I have di&s;|covered,
and prepared with infinite la|bour.&mdash;Sir,
I have lately cured a wo|man
in Bri&s;tol&mdash;a common pro&s;titute,
&s;ir, who had got all the wor&s;t &s;ymp|toms
of the di&s;order; &s;uch as <HI>nodi, to|phi,</HI>
and <HI>gummata, verrucae, cri&s;tae
Galli,</HI> and a <HI>&s;erpiginous</HI> eruption, or
rather a pocky itch all over her body.
&mdash;By that time &s;he had taken the
&s;econd pill, &s;ir, by Heaven! &s;he was
as &s;mooth as my hand, and the third
<PB N="31" REF="44">
made her as &s;ound and as fre&s;h as a
