<P>As I have &s;omething el&s;e to &s;ay; and
this letter has run to an uncon&s;cionable
length, I &s;hall now give you a little re|&s;pite,
and trouble you again by the very
fir&s;t po&s;t. I wi&s;h you would take it in
your head to retaliate the&s;e double &s;trokes
upon</P>
<CLOSER>Yours always,
<SIGNED>J. MELFORD.</SIGNED></CLOSER>
